yeah just saw that the service was removed in next change, thanks.
looks like the previous fixup_router is not there, it will be nice to have that.

It shouldn't be needed now that we are route setting manually. I've done a bunch of iterations on hardware and haven't seen the route missing yet.

It would be nice if we could reproduce the original issue, because the fixup route thing was a hack for a single network setting that we shouldn't need.

ok, since we have everything in one place now, it will be easier to just have a recovery function that verify everything and redo the configuration if necessary, I can look into it in a separate change.
